<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2499/97 of 15 December 1997 amending Regulation (EC) No 2012/96 opening and providing for the administration of a Community tariff quota for grape juice and must as from the 1996/97 marketing year </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2499/97, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2012/96, millega avatakse viinamarjamahla ja -virret h&otilde;lmav &uuml;henduse tariifikvoot ning s&auml;testatakse selle haldamine alates turustusaastast 1996/97 15. detsember 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 1095/96 of 18 June 1996 on the implementation of the concessions set out in Schedule CXL drawn up in the wake of the conclusion of the GATT XXIV.6 negotiations (1), and in particular Article 1 (1) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 18. juuni 1996. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1095/96 GATTi XXIV artikli l&otilde;ike 6 alusel toimunud l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimiste tulemusena koostatud CXL loendis s&auml;testatud kontsessioonide rakendamise kohta, (1) eriti selle artikli 1 l&otilde;iget 1, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EC) No 2012/96 (2) introduces a Community tariff quota for 14 000 tonnes of imported grape juice and must and provides for exemption from the specific duty per hectolitre pursuant to the agreement concluded as part of the World Trade Organisation multilateral trade negotiations; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Maailma Kaubandusorganisatsiooni mitmepoolsete kaubandusl&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimiste osana s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel kehtestatakse komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2012/96 (2) viinamarjamahla ja -virde importi h&otilde;lmav &uuml;henduse tariifikvoot 14 000 tonnile ja s&auml;testatakse hektoliitri kohta m&auml;&auml;ratud koguselisest tollimaksust vabastamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas access to that quota is subject to certain specific conditions concerning the use of the imported products; whereas compliance with those conditions is ensured by a security lodged by the importer on release for free circulation of the products with the customs service of the Member State concerned; whereas that security is to be equal to the specific duty waived; whereas the security is to be released forthwith in respect of imported quantities for which the operator provides proof that the products have been used for the purpose specified in the import licence; whereas experience has shown that transport between release for free circulation and the end use specified in the import licence may give rise to many forms of handling; whereas such handling may entail repackaging and may result in residues in containers, tanks or pumping equipment; whereas circumstances therefore exist that are likely to prevent 100 % proof of utilisation of the quantities imported from being obtained; whereas a tolerance should therefore be fixed for any losses due to such handling and transport; whereas provision should accordingly be made for the security to be released in full where proof is provided that the products have been used for the purpose specified in the import licence, subject to a certain tolerance; </inglise>
<eesti> selle kvoodi kasutusv&otilde;imaluse suhtes kehtivad teatavad importtoodete kasutamise eritingimused; nende tingimuste t&auml;itmine tagatakse toodete vabasse ringlusse lubamisel importija poolt asjaomase liikmesriigi tolliasutusele antava tagatisega; see tagatis peab olema v&otilde;rdne koguselise tollimaksuga, mida kvoodi piires ei kohaldata; tagatis vabastatakse kohe nende imporditud koguste suhtes, mille osas ettev&otilde;tja t&otilde;endab, et tooteid on kasutatud impordilitsentsil n&auml;idatud eesm&auml;rgil; kogemused on n&auml;idanud, et toodete vedu alates nende vabasse ringlusse lubamisest kuni impordilitsentsil t&auml;psustatud l&otilde;ppkasutuseni v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada mitut erinevat k&auml;itlemist; nende k&auml;itlemiste hulka v&otilde;ib kuuluda &uuml;mberpakendamine, mist&otilde;ttu mahutitesse, tsisternidesse v&otilde;i pumbaseadmetesse v&otilde;ib j&auml;&auml;da tootej&auml;&auml;ke; seet&otilde;ttu ei saa teatavate asjaolude korral t&otilde;endada, et imporditud kogused on 100% ulatuses &auml;ra kasutatud; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks k&auml;itlemisest ja veost p&otilde;hjustatud kadude suhtes kehtestada lubatud h&auml;lve; vastavalt tuleks ette n&auml;ha tagatise t&auml;ielik vabastamine, kui t&otilde;endatakse, et tooteid on kasutatud impordilitsentsil n&auml;idatud eesm&auml;rgil teatava lubatud h&auml;lbe piires; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas such losses may have affected products imported since the entry into force of Regulation (EC) No 2012/96; whereas this Regulation should apply to operators who so request in respect of the imports referred to above; </inglise>
<eesti> sellised kaod v&otilde;isid olla tekkinud toodete importimisel p&auml;rast m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2012/96 j&otilde;ustumist; k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tteid tuleks kohaldada nende ettev&otilde;tjate suhtes, kes seda &uuml;lalnimetatud importi silmas pidades n&otilde;uavad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Wine, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las veinituru korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The following sentence is hereby added to Article 5 (b) of Regulation (EC) No 2012/96: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2012/96 artikli 5 punktile b lisatakse j&auml;rgmine lause: </eesti>
<inglise> 'The security referred to herein shall be released in full once the operator has provided proof that the whole quantity of products imported has been used for the purpose specified, subject to a tolerance of 1 % of such quantities to cover losses verified and certified by the competent inspection body and resulting from handling and transport between release for free circulation and utilisation for the purpose concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> "Eespool nimetatud tagatis vabastatakse t&auml;ielikult, kui ettev&otilde;tja on t&otilde;endanud, et kogu imporditud toodete kogus on litsentsil n&auml;idatud eesm&auml;rgil &auml;ra kasutatud 1% lubatud h&auml;lbe piires; h&auml;lve katab p&auml;deva inspekteerimisorgani poolt kontrollitud ja kinnitatud kaod, mis on tekkinud toodete k&auml;itlemisel ja veol alates nende vabasse ringlusse lubamisest kuni n&auml;idatud kasutuseni. </eesti>
<inglise> That tolerance shall not apply in cases of force majeure. </inglise>
<eesti> Lubatud h&auml;lvet ei kohaldata v&auml;&auml;ramatu j&otilde;u korral." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> On application by the operators, this Regulation may apply to products released for free circulation from 25 October 1996 in respect of which proof has not yet been provided that the whole quantity imported has been used for the purpose specified in the import licence. </inglise>
<eesti> Ettev&otilde;tjate taotlusel v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tteid kohaldada alates 25. oktoobrist 1996 vabasse ringlusse lubatud toodete suhtes, mille osas kogu imporditud koguse &auml;rakasutamist impordilitsentsil n&auml;idatud eesm&auml;rgil ei ole veel t&otilde;endatud. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 15 December 1997. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 15. detsember 1997 </eesti>
